## SIL analysis

Dumping the function immediately before the crashing CopyPropagation run (`-Xllvm -sil-print-function=<mangled> -Xllvm -sil-print-before=copy-propagation`, capture from the originating app build — value numbers differ from the single-file repro but the shape is identical) shows the invalid ownership already present in the pass **input**. Each of the three predecessors of the merge block ends the borrow *before* branching:

```sil
bb37(%506 : @guaranteed $ActivityJSONValue):      // Preds: bb35
  ...
  %510 = enum $Optional<ActivityJSONValue>, #Optional.some!enumelt, %508
  %511 = struct_element_addr %0, #HouseholdMember.color
  %512 = load_borrow %511                         // users: %515, %514
  ...
  end_borrow %512                                 // id: %514
  br bb40(%510, %512)                             // id: %515   <-- borrowed value passed AFTER end_borrow
```

and the merge block receives the dead-borrowed String as a guaranteed phi with an **empty enclosing-values list**:

```sil
bb40(%535 : @owned $Optional<ActivityJSONValue>, %536 : @guaranteed $String): // Preds: bb38 bb37 bb39
  %537 = borrowed %536 from ()                    // <-- no enclosing borrow
  debug_value %537, let, name "$0", argno 1       // inlined body of Optional.map's closure
  ...
```

`bb40` is the inlined `.map { .string($0) }` closure body of the *second* `jsonValue` call (`%536` is `$0`); the three predecessors are the `.some`/`.none`/`??`-merge paths of the *first*, already-inlined `jsonValue` call, each of which separately `load_borrow`s the same `String` field as the second call's argument. The same function had survived three earlier CopyPropagation runs in the pipeline; the broken shape appears only after later inlining rounds, suggesting the block-duplication/jump-threading of the always-`.some` `switch_enum` chain fails to extend the `load_borrow` scope across the branch it creates (or fails to model the guaranteed phi as a reborrow).

## Environment

- Apple Swift version 6.3.3 (swiftlang-6.3.3.1.3 clang-2100.1.1.101), swift-driver 1.148.6
- Xcode 26.6 (17F113), macOS 26.x (Darwin 25.3.0), Apple Silicon
- Single-file repro verified against `-target arm64-apple-ios26.1-simulator` (iPhoneSimulator26.5 SDK); the originating app crashed identically building for iOS simulator and native macOS

## Possibly related (checked; different shapes)

- #90408 — ownership verification failure also *detected by* CopyPropagation at -O, but a 6.4-dev regression (6.3.2 fine there) with a `ByteSlice` phi consumed by `fix_lifetime`. This report crashes on released 6.3.3 with a `load_borrow` → guaranteed-phi shape from `Optional.map`/`??` inlining.
- #78447 — same verifier message in Jan-2025 snapshots (`begin_borrow` + `mark_dependence`, C interop); fixed via #78482.

